answer: Fairly normal, considering. Notably you are talking about "within a category_id" that you don't seem to be attempting to filter on in the query. If there are things that cut down results then add them to the query. MongoDB also "puports" to be reasonable about index order of fields, but I would consider it good practice still to implement the compound index fields in the most commonly used order, and order of what is likely to filter down results the most. Doing so will reduce scans. Also note that geospatial queries notoriously misreport scanned items
